Rating: 4
My husband and I love this recipe. I cut down on prep time by subsituting a jar of mango pineapple salsa. I like the extra kick the salsa brings to the recipe. I also marinated the chops in a curry sauce which added an extra depth of flavor and went well with the fruityness of the mango/pineapple sauce.

Rating: 3
This recipe is a keeper. Served with juicy pork cops and coconut rice, it's a delicious summer meal.I used a potato masher instead of a food processor to puree and it worked fine. I would advise using fresh, not canned fruit, if you want a less sweet flavor. I didn't have any light brown sugar, so I substituted regular sugar and added a touch of molasses. The sauce works well with firm fish and chicken, too.

