Rating: 3
The sauce is flavorful, tangy and not too sweet, and it's what makes this dish stand out. Although the recipe called for fresh mango and canned pineapple, I couldn't get a decent fresh mango, so I used canned, and it was fine. It might be fun to try with fresh of both fruits in season, though. The sauce would also work very well with roasted loin (or tenderloin) of pork or with chicken, and it would be just the thing to zip up reheated turkey leftovers. I served it with basmati rice and omitted the cilantro.